article.headline: UC Davis 64, Loyola Marymount 55
article.story: AMES, Iowa -- Joe Harden scored 16 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead UC Davis past Loyola-Marymount 64-55 on Sunday to wrap up the World Vision Classic. Kyle Brucculeri and Dominic Calegari each posted 14 points for the Aggies. Mark Payne had seven assists. The Aggies took a 28-14 early lead when Calegari hit a pair of 3s and Brucculeri added his own basket from outside the arc. UC Davis kept a healthy lead for the remainder of the game. A dunk from Ashley Hamilton and free throws from Vernon Teel put the Lions within eight points. UC Davis answered back when Harden drove through the paint for 2 then Brucculeri connected on a 3-pointer after a steal. Teel scored 23 points and had 6 rebounds to lead the Lions. Loyola-Marymount headed home 0-3 while UC Davis picked up its first win of the season.
